@node Program versions
@title "Program versions"

@{b}@{u}Program versions@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}@{u}FLMconv:@{ub}@{uu}

@{u}V2.05:@{uu}
- locale strings completed
- some internal changes

@{u}V2.00:@{uu}
- sorting of dictionaries with help of quick sort faster
- you need less RAM
- bug fixing (remove of double words)

@{u}V1.10:@{uu}
- bug fixing
- you can create shareware or registered dictionaries
- you can create ASCII dictionaries

@{u}V1.03:@{uu}
- some internal changes
- localisation
- font sensitive

@{u}V1.02:@{uu}
- dictionary conversion was optimized

@{u}V1.01:@{uu}
- first released version

@{u}V1.00:@{uu}
- first internal beta version




@{b}@{u}FLMc:@{ub}@{uu}

@{u}V1.15:@{uu}
- see FLM V2.31

@{u}V1.14:@{uu}
- locale strings completed

@{u}V1.13:@{uu}
- see FLM V2.24 (*)

@{u}V1.12:@{uu}
- see FLM V2.23

@{u}V1.11:@{uu}
- see FLM V2.22 (*)

@{u}V1.10:@{uu}
- see FLM V2.20
- see FLM V2.21

@{u}V1.10a:@{uu}
- see FLM V2.20a (*)
- dictionaries now loaded after first call

@{u}V1.05:@{uu}
- see FLM V2.151
- see FLM V2.152

@{u}V1.04:@{uu}
- now you can close the Workbench while FLMc is running

@{u}V1.03:@{uu}
- see FLM V2.14 (*)
- now ToolType @{" NOPUBLICSCREENS " link FLM Commodity} works properly

@{u}V1.02:@{uu}
- input text field is already active at the opening of the dictionary
  window
- through ESC you can close the dictionary window

@{u}V1.01:@{uu}
- program size was cut down about of 10 KBytes

@{u}V1.00:@{uu}
- first commodity version




@{b}@{u}FLM:@{ub}@{uu}

@{u}V2.31:@{uu}
- recompiled with UAE for windows
- correct my address

@{u}V2.31:@{uu}
- error at sorting on listboxes with more than one dictionary removed
- error in search mode #? with more than one dictionary removed
- listbox width for standard dictionary can be changed
- expanded super dictionaries with ca. 5000 words

@{u}V2.30:@{uu}
- online help now with AmigaGuide
- protocol of learning
- bug fixing

@{u}V2.22:@{uu}
- learning with time limit should now work
- window handling is now better
- endless standard and thesaurus dictionaries
- if you have lesser than 10000 Byte FLM will bring a message (*)
- any little changes
- bug fixing

@{u}V2.21:@{uu}
- FLM.catalog couldn't be used (FLM says false version)
- error at buffering of dictionaries (any words were not right wrote
  to listbox)

@{u}V2.20:@{uu}
- bug fixing
- you can change the buffer size (see @{" Dictionary Settings " link HLP_WBEINST})
- search in mode IN and #? from harddisk is now faster

@{u}V2.20b:@{uu}
- new ARexx commands @{b}@{ub}@{" SETMODE " link ARexx support}, @{b}@{ub}@{" VERSION " link ARexx support}, @{b}@{ub}@{" LOAD " link ARexx support}, @{b}@{ub}@{" OPENWIN " link ARexx support}, @{b}@{" CLOSEWIN " link ARexx support}@{ub}
- new dictionary Irregular verbs
- bug fixing

@{u}V2.20a:@{uu}
- online help now also for error messages
- new search mode with wildcards (*)
- time limit for learning vocables
- dictionaries you can now use parallel

@{u}V2.17:@{uu}
- French online help

@{u}V2.16:@{uu}
- English online help

@{u}V2.152:@{uu}
- bug fixing
- now words can be changed through cursor keys
- RETURN and/or ENTER key(s) bring(s) you to the input field
- ESC allows you to close the active window

@{u}V2.151:@{uu}
- bug fixing (crashed on a 68000-based machine)

@{u}V2.15:@{uu}
- bug fixing
- added ARexx commands @{" FOUND " link ARexx support} and @{" TAKEFOUND " link ARexx support}

@{u}V2.14:@{uu}
- cut down RAM needs for word entries about of 50% (*)
- speeded up word searching (*)
- added ARexx command @{" SETLANGUAGE " link ARexx support}

@{u}V2.13:@{uu}
- added a commodity version
- some small internal changes

@{u}V2.12:@{uu}
- more presets
- expanded program documentation

@{u}V2.11:@{uu}
- now the ARexx port can be called anywhere from FLM (also in learning
  mode...)
- @{" ToolTypes " link ToolTypes} support
- with the help of Enforcer eliminated a couple of unauthorized memory
  access
- now Standard and Thesaurus dictionary can be scaled too
- and eliminated another couple of bugs
- expanded and corrected Super dictionary about of 5,000 key words

@{u}V2.10:@{uu}
- localisation (now FLM uses the flm.catalog, so far this is available)
- eliminated some other small bugs
- made some smaller improvements
- now the ARexx dictionary window can be scaled

@{u}V2.10a:@{uu}
- eliminated some small bugs
- made some smaller improvements
- improved ARexx scripts to customise FLM with word processors and text
  editors (if haven't yet started FLM, it's started from its script)
- expanded Super dictionary approx. 5000 key words (120 Kbytes)

@{u}V2.03: internal version - it was never published@{uu}
- added a Font setting
- new config file, which is not compatible with the old one

@{u}V2.02: was only available as alpha version@{uu}
- added ARexx commands QUIT and @{" WORDANZ " link ARexx support}
- expanded ARexx command @{" TAKEWORD " link ARexx support}
- now ARexx port is already in the start window at user disposal
- removed menu command "Open ARexx Port"

@{u}V2.01@{uu}
- eliminated some minor bugs
- now searching in "#?" mode from disk lasts only still half so long

@{u}V2.00@{uu}
- facing EnglischGenius, FLM was programmed in C++ from scratch, and
  adapted to Workbench 2.0
- added 160,000 entries in dictionaries English/German & German/English

@{u}V1.0@{uu}
- this FLM version was not officially released as FLM 2.0 is the successor
  to EnglishGenius 1.0

@{u}V0.?@{uu}
- here it deals with the program FLM Light
@endnode

@node Known bugs
@title "Known bugs"

@{b}@{u}Known bugs@{ub}@{uu}

- for ex. the font size 16 no more matches the screen layout

All above bugs are unattractive for the FLM appearance but don't prevent
you from working with it.

@endnode

